used by Kerby components that need interoperable binary serialization.\",\nmetadata/org.apache.kerby/kerby-xdr/index.json:26:    \"description\" : \"Apache Kerby Kerby XDR provides Java support for encoding and decoding External Data Representation (XDR) data structures within the Apache Kerby project. It supplies XDR primitive and structured types plus stream utilities used by Kerby components that need interoperable binary serialization.\",\nmetadata/org.apache.parquet/parquet-encoding/index.json:9:    \"description\" : \"Apache Parquet Encodings provides Java implementations of the encodings and bit-packing codecs used to read and write Parquet column values. It is part of Apache Parquet's Java stack and supports compression-independent serialization of typed column data for Parquet files.\",\nmetadata/org.apache.parquet/parquet-jackson/index.json:9:    \"description\" : \"Apache Parquet Jackson is the Parquet Java module that packages shaded Jackson libraries for use by Apache Parquet. It relocates Jackson classes under shaded.parquet.com.fasterxml.jackson so Parquet components can perform JSON serialization and parsing while avoiding dependency conflicts with applications.\",\nmetadata/org.json4s/json4s-scalap_2.13/index.json:9:    \"description\" : \"json4s-scalap provides json4s' embedded scalap implementation for reading Scala signature metadata from compiled classes. It parses class files and ScalaSig information so json4s reflection-based extraction and serialization can understand Scala symbols, types, and constructors.\",\nmetadata/org.json4s/json4s-jackson_3/index.json:9:    \"description\" : \"Json4s is a Scala JSON library that provides a shared JSON AST plus parsing, querying, transformation, extraction, and serialization APIs. The json4s-jackson artifact supplies the Jackson-backed parser and serializer integration for using that AST on Scala 3/JVM projects.\",\nmetadata/org.json4s/json4s-jackson_2.13/index.json:9:    \"description\" : \"Json4s is a Scala JSON library that provides a shared JSON AST plus parsing, querying, transformation, extraction, and serialization APIs. The json4s-jackson artifact supplies the Jackson-backed parser and serializer integration for using that AST on Scala 2/JVM projects.\",\nmetadata/org.json4s/json4s-jackson_2.13/index.json:32:    \"description\" : \"Json4s is a Scala JSON library that provides a shared JSON AST plus parsing, querying, transformation, extraction, and serialization APIs. The json4s-jackson artifact supplies the Jackson-backed parser and serializer integration for using that AST on Scala 2/JVM projects.\",\nmetadata/org.json4s/json4s-native_3/index.json:9:    \"description\" : \"Json4s is a Scala JSON library that provides a shared JSON AST plus parsing, transformation, extraction, and serialization APIs. The json4s-native artifact supplies the native parser and serialization implementation, avoiding the Jackson backend while targeting Scala 3 on the JVM.\",\nmetadata/org.osgi/core/4.3.0/reachability-metadata.json:227:  \"serialization\": [\nmetadata/org.json4s/json4s-scalap_3/index.json:9:    \"description\" : \"json4s-scalap provides json4s' embedded scalap implementation for reading Scala signature metadata from compiled classes. It parses class files and ScalaSig information so json4s reflection-based extraction and serialization can understand Scala symbols, types, and constructors.\",\nmetadata/org.osgi/org.osgi.core/4.3.0/reachability-metadata.json:227:  \"serialization\": [\nmetadata/org.osgi/org.osgi.core/4.3.1/reachability-metadata.json:59:  \"serialization\": [\nmetadata/org.jetbrains.kotlinx/kotlinx-serialization-cbor-jvm/index.json:5:    \"source-code-url\" : \"https://repo.maven.apache.org/maven2/org/jetbrains/kotlinx/kotlinx-serialization-cbor-jvm/$version$/kotlinx-serialization-cbor-jvm-$version$-sources.jar\",\nmetadata/org.jetbrains.kotlinx/kotlinx-serialization-cbor-jvm/index.json:6:    \"repository-url\" : \"https://github.com/Kotlin/kotlinx.serialization\",\nmetadata/org.jetbrains.kotlinx/kotlinx-serialization-cbor-jvm/index.json:7:    \"test-code-url\" : \"https://github.com/Kotlin/kotlinx.serialization/tree/v$version$/formats/cbor/jvmTest\",\nmetadata/org.jetbrains.kotlinx/kotlinx-serialization-cbor-jvm/index.json:8:    \"documentation-url\" : \"https://github.com/Kotlin/kotlinx.serialization/blob/v$version$/docs/formats.md#cbor-experimental\",\nmetadata/org.jetbrains.kotlinx/kotlinx-serialization-cbor-jvm/index.json:9:    \"description\" : \"kotlinx-serialization-cbor-jvm is the JVM artifact for kotlinx.serialization's CBOR format, enabling Kotlin serialization to encode and decode objects as Concise Binary Object Representation byte arrays. It supplies the Cbor format, CBOR-specific annotations, configuration, encoders, decoders, and internal readers/writers for JVM applications.\",\nmetadata/org.jetbrains.kotlinx/kotlinx-serialization-cbor-jvm/index.json:20:      \"kotlinx.serialization.cbor\"\nmetadata/org.jetbrains.kotlinx/kotlinx-serialization-json-okio-jvm/index.json:5:    \"source-code-url\" : \"https://repo.maven.apache.org/maven2/org/jetbrains/kotlinx/kotlinx-serialization-json-okio-jvm/$version$/kotlinx-serialization-json-okio-jvm-$version$-sources.jar\",\nmetadata/org.jetbrains.kotlinx/kotlinx-serialization-json-okio-jvm/index.json:6:    \"repository-url\" : \"https://github.com/Kotlin/kotlinx.serialization\",\nmetadata/org.jetbrains.kotlinx/kotlinx-serialization-json-okio-jvm/index.json:7:    \"test-code-url\" : \"https://github.com/Kotlin/kotlinx.serialization/tree/v$version$/formats/json-okio/commonTest\",\nmetadata/org.jetbrains.kotlinx/kotlinx-serialization-json-okio-jvm/index.json:8:    \"documentation-url\" : \"https://javadoc.io/doc/org.jetbrains.kotlinx/kotlinx-serialization-json-okio-jvm/$version$/index.html\",\nmetadata/org.jetbrains.kotlinx/kotlinx-serialization-json-okio-jvm/index.json:9:    \"description\" : \"kotlinx-serialization-json-okio-jvm adds Okio integration for kotlinx.serialization JSON on the JVM, letting Json encode values to BufferedSink and decode values from BufferedSource. It provides experimental streaming and sequence helpers for Kotlin/JVM applications that use Okio for buffered I/O.\",\nmetadata/org.jetbrains.kotlinx/kotlinx-serialization-json-okio-jvm/index.json:18:      \"kotlinx.serialization.json.okio\"\nmetadata/org.jetbrains.kotlinx/kotlinx-serialization-core-jvm/index.json:5:    \"source-code-url\" : \"https://repo1.maven.org/maven2/org/jetbrains/kotlinx/kotlinx-serialization-core-jvm/$version$/kotlinx-serialization-core-jvm-$version$-sources.jar\",\nmetadata/org.jetbrains.kotlinx/kotlinx-serialization-core-jvm/index.json:6:    \"repository-url\" : \"https://github.com/Kotlin/kotlinx.serialization\",\nmetadata/org.jetbrains.kotlinx/kotlinx-serialization-core-jvm/index.json:7:    \"test-code-url\" : \"https://github.com/Kotlin/kotlinx.serialization/tree/v$version$/core/jvmTest\",\nmetadata/org.jetbrains.kotlinx/kotlinx-serialization-core-jvm/index.json:8:    \"documentation-url\" : \"https://github.com/Kotlin/kotlinx.serialization/tree/v$version$/docs\",\nmetadata/org.jetbrains.kotlinx/kotlinx-serialization-core-jvm/index.json:9:    \"description\" : \"kotlinx-serialization-core-jvm is the JVM runtime core for Kotlin serialization, providing serializers, descriptors, encoding and decoding abstractions, and module support used by format implementations. It supports Kotlin multiplatform serialization on the JVM and is used together with format modules such as JSON, CBOR, ProtoBuf, and Properties.\",\nmetadata/org.jetbrains.kotlinx/kotlinx-serialization-core-jvm/index.json:20:      \"kotlinx.serialization\"\nmetadata/org.apache.activemq/artemis-core-client/2.33.0/reachability-metadata.json:277:  \"serialization\" : [\nmetadata/com.google.code.gson/gson/index.json:9:    \"description\" : \"Gson is a Java library for converting Java objects to and from JSON. It provides object mapping, tree, and streaming APIs for JSON serialization and deserialization.\",\nmetadata/com.google.code.gson/gson/index.json:33:    \"description\" : \"Gson is a Java library for converting Java objects to and from JSON. It provides object mapping, tree, and streaming APIs for JSON serialization and deserialization.\",\nmetadata/org.jetbrains.kotlinx/kotlinx-serialization-properties-jvm/index.json:5:    \"source-code-url\" : \"https://repo.maven.apache.org/maven2/org/jetbrains/kotlinx/kotlinx-serialization-properties-jvm/$version$/kotlinx-serialization-properties-jvm-$version$-sources.jar\",\nmetadata/org.jetbrains.kotlinx/kotlinx-serialization-properties-jvm/index.json:6:    \"repository-url\" : \"https://github.com/Kotlin/kotlinx.serialization\",\nmetadata/org.jetbrains.kotlinx/kotlinx-serialization-properties-jvm/index.json:7:    \"test-code-url\" : \"https://github.com/Kotlin/kotlinx.serialization/tree/v$version$/formats/properties/commonTest\",\nmetadata/org.jetbrains.kotlinx/kotlinx-serialization-properties-jvm/index.json:8:    \"documentation-url\" : \"https://github.com/Kotlin/kotlinx.serialization/blob/v$version$/docs/formats.md#properties-experimental\",\nmetadata/org.jetbrains.kotlinx/kotlinx-serialization-properties-jvm/index.json:9:    \"description\" : \"kotlinx-serialization-properties-jvm provides the JVM artifact for the experimental Properties format in kotlinx.serialization. It serializes Kotlin @Serializable values to flat property maps with string keys and primitive values, and decodes those maps back into typed objects.\",\nmetadata/org.jetbrains.kotlinx/kotlinx-serialization-properties-jvm/index.json:18:      \"kotlinx.serialization.properties\"\nmetadata/com.github.plokhotnyuk.jsoniter-scala/jsoniter-scala-core_3/index.json:9:    \"description\" : \"jsoniter-scala-core provides the runtime JSON reader, writer, and codec APIs for jsoniter-scala, a Scala JSON parsing and serialization library. It focuses on safe, high-performance conversion between JSON input and Scala/JVM values with low allocation and support for custom codecs.\",\nmetadata/org.jetbrains.kotlinx/kotlinx-serialization-json/index.json:4:    \"reason\": \"The published root JAR contains Kotlin Multiplatform metadata/linkdata and no JVM class files; Gradle module metadata redirects standard JVM variants to org.jetbrains.kotlinx:kotlinx-serialization-json-jvm:1.9.0.\",\nmetadata/org.jetbrains.kotlinx/kotlinx-serialization-json/index.json:5:    \"replacement\": \"org.jetbrains.kotlinx:kotlinx-serialization-json-jvm:1.9.0\"\nmetadata/org.jetbrains.kotlinx/kotlinx-serialization-json-io-jvm/index.json:5:    \"source-code-url\" : \"https://repo.maven.apache.org/maven2/org/jetbrains/kotlinx/kotlinx-serialization-json-io-jvm/$version$/kotlinx-serialization-json-io-jvm-$version$-sources.jar\",\nmetadata/org.jetbrains.kotlinx/kotlinx-serialization-json-io-jvm/index.json:6:    \"repository-url\" : \"https://github.com/Kotlin/kotlinx.serialization\",\nmetadata/org.jetbrains.kotlinx/kotlinx-serialization-json-io-jvm/index.json:7:    \"test-code-url\" : \"https://github.com/Kotlin/kotlinx.serialization/tree/v$version$/formats/json-io/commonTest\",\nmetadata/org.jetbrains.kotlinx/kotlinx-serialization-json-io-jvm/index.json:8:    \"documentation-url\" : \"https://javadoc.io/doc/org.jetbrains.kotlinx/kotlinx-serialization-json-io-jvm/$version$/index.html\",\nmetadata/org.jetbrains.kotlinx/kotlinx-serialization-json-io-jvm/index.json:9:    \"description\" : \"kotlinx-serialization-json-io-jvm adds kotlinx-io Source and Sink integration for kotlinx.serialization JSON on the JVM. It provides experimental APIs to encode Kotlin @Serializable values to UTF-8 JSON sinks, decode values from sources, and lazily read sequences of JSON elements.\",\nmetadata/org.jetbrains.kotlinx/kotlinx-serialization-json-io-jvm/index.json:21:      \"kotlinx.serialization.json.io\"\nmetadata/org.jetbrains.kotlinx/kotlinx-serialization-hocon/index.json:5:    \"source-code-url\" : \"https://repo1.maven.org/maven2/org/jetbrains/kotlinx/kotlinx-serialization-hocon/$version$/kotlinx-serialization-hocon-$version$-sources.jar\",\nmetadata/org.jetbrains.kotlinx/kotlinx-serialization-hocon/index.json:6:    \"repository-url\" : \"https://github.com/Kotlin/kotlinx.serialization\",\nmetadata/org.jetbrains.kotlinx/kotlinx-serialization-hocon/index.json:7:    \"test-code-url\" : \"https://github.com/Kotlin/kotlinx.serialization/tree/v$version$/formats/hocon/src/test\",\nmetadata/org.jetbrains.kotlinx/kotlinx-serialization-hocon/index.json:8:    \"documentation-url\" : \"https://github.com/Kotlin/kotlinx.serialization/blob/v$version$/formats/README.md#hocon\",\nmetadata/org.jetbrains.kotlinx/kotlinx-serialization-hocon/index.json:9:    \"description\" : \"kotlinx-serialization-hocon is the JVM-only HOCON format module for kotlinx.serialization, backed by Lightbend Config. It decodes Typesafe Config objects into Kotlin serializable classes and provides HOCON encoders/decoders plus serializers for Java Duration and ConfigMemorySize values.\",\nmetadata/org.jetbrains.kotlinx/kotlinx-serialization-hocon/index.json:18:      \"kotlinx.serialization.hocon\"\nmetadata/org.jetbrains.kotlinx/kotlinx-serialization-core/index.json:4:    \"reason\": \"The published root JAR contains Kotlin metadata/linkdata and no JVM class files; Gradle module metadata redirects standard JVM variants to org.jetbrains.kotlinx:kotlinx-serialization-core-jvm:1.9.0.\",\nmetadata/org.jetbrains.kotlinx/kotlinx-serialization-core/index.json:5:    \"replacement\": \"org.jetbrains.kotlinx:kotlinx-serialization-core-jvm:1.9.0\"\nmetadata/org.jetbrains.kotlinx/kotlinx-serialization-json-jvm/index.json:5:    \"source-code-url\" : \"https://repo.maven.apache.org/maven2/org/jetbrains/kotlinx/kotlinx-serialization-json-jvm/$version$/kotlinx-serialization-json-jvm-$version$-sources.jar\",\nmetadata/org.jetbrains.kotlinx/kotlinx-serialization-json-jvm/index.json:6:    \"repository-url\" : \"https://github.com/Kotlin/kotlinx.serialization\",\nmetadata/org.jetbrains.kotlinx/kotlinx-serialization-json-jvm/index.json:7:    \"test-code-url\" : \"https://github.com/Kotlin/kotlinx.serialization/tree/v$version$/formats/json-tests/jvmTest\",\nmetadata/org.jetbrains.kotlinx/kotlinx-serialization-json-jvm/index.json:8:    \"documentation-url\" : \"https://github.com/Kotlin/kotlinx.serialization/blob/v$version$/docs/json.md\",\nmetadata/org.jetbrains.kotlinx/kotlinx-serialization-json-jvm/index.json:9:    \"description\" : \"kotlinx-serialization-json-jvm is the JVM artifact for kotlinx.serialization's JSON format, providing APIs to encode and decode @Serializable Kotlin objects and JSON tree values. It supports configurable parsing and rendering features such as polymorphism, naming strategies, unknown-key handling, default handling, and streaming and sequence helpers for Kotlin/JVM applications.\",\nmetadata/org.jetbrains.kotlinx/kotlinx-serialization-json-jvm/index.json:21:      \"kotlinx.serialization.json\"\nmetadata/io.suzaku/boopickle_2.13/index.json:9:    \"description\" : \"BooPickle is a Scala binary serialization library for pickling and unpickling values into compact ByteBuffer data. It supports primitives, collections, options, tuples, case classes, custom serializers, references, and deduplication without reflection across JVM, Scala.js, and Scala Native.\",\nmetadata/io.suzaku/boopickle_3/index.json:9:    \"description\" : \"BooPickle is a Scala binary serialization library for pickling and unpickling values into compact ByteBuffer data. It supports primitives, collections, options, tuples, case classes, custom serializers, references, and deduplication without reflection across JVM, Scala.js, and Scala Native.\",\nmetadata/org.quartz-scheduler/quartz/2.3.2/reachability-metadata.json:156:  \"serialization\": [\nmetadata/jakarta.json.bind/jakarta.json.bind-api/index.json:9:    \"description\" : \"Jakarta JSON Binding (JSON-B) is a standard API for converting Java objects to and from JSON documents. It defines default object mapping behavior and annotations and SPIs that allow applications and implementations to customize serialization and deserialization.\",\nmetadata/com.softwaremill.sttp.model/core_3/index.json:9:    \"description\" : \"sttp model provides Scala HTTP model classes such as URI, method, status code, media type, headers, query parameters, multipart parts, and server-sent events. It includes parsing and serialization helpers for these values and is used by sttp client and tapir as a shared HTTP modeling layer.\",\nmetadata/org.jetbrains.kotlinx/kotlinx-serialization-protobuf-jvm/index.json:5:    \"source-code-url\" : \"https://repo.maven.apache.org/maven2/org/jetbrains/kotlinx/kotlinx-serialization-protobuf-jvm/$version$/kotlinx-serialization-protobuf-jvm-$version$-sources.jar\",\nmetadata/org.jetbrains.kotlinx/kotlinx-serialization-protobuf-jvm/index.json:6:    \"repository-url\" : \"https://github.com/Kotlin/kotlinx.serialization\",\nmetadata/org.jetbrains.kotlinx/kotlinx-serialization-protobuf-jvm/index.json:7:    \"test-code-url\" : \"https://github.com/Kotlin/kotlinx.serialization/tree/v$version$/formats/protobuf/jvmTest\",\nmetadata/org.jetbrains.kotlinx/kotlinx-serialization-protobuf-jvm/index.json:8:    \"documentation-url\" : \"https://github.com/Kotlin/kotlinx.serialization/blob/v$version$/docs/formats.md#protobuf-experimental\",\nmetadata/org.jetbrains.kotlinx/kotlinx-serialization-protobuf-jvm/index.json:9:    \"description\" : \"kotlinx-serialization-protobuf-jvm is the JVM artifact of kotlinx.serialization's ProtoBuf format, providing APIs to encode and decode @Serializable Kotlin objects as Protocol Buffers binary data. It supports field-number annotations, integer encoding options, packed fields, oneof-style polymorphism, and schema generation for Kotlin/JVM applications using kotlinx.serialization.\",\nmetadata/org.jetbrains.kotlinx/kotlinx-serialization-protobuf-jvm/index.json:20:      \"kotlinx.serialization.protobuf\"\n