ers and runtime services. It defines bootstrap, deployment, resource, transaction, security, validation, EJB, injection, servlet, and serialization contracts for container integration.\",\nmetadata/org.jboss.weld/weld-spi/index.json:89:    \"description\" : \"Weld SPI provides the service-provider interfaces used to integrate Weld, the CDI reference implementation, with Java EE containers and runtime services. It defines bootstrap, deployment, resource, transaction, security, validation, EJB, injection, servlet, and serialization contracts for container integration.\",\nmetadata/org.jboss.weld/weld-spi/index.json:103:    \"description\" : \"Weld SPI provides the service-provider interfaces used to integrate Weld, the CDI reference implementation, with Java EE containers and runtime services. It defines bootstrap, deployment, resource, transaction, security, validation, EJB, injection, servlet, and serialization contracts for container integration.\",\nmetadata/org.jboss.netty/netty/3.2.2.Final/reachability-metadata.json:5:        \"typeReached\" : \"org.jboss.netty.handler.codec.serialization.CompactObjectInputStream\"\nmetadata/org.jboss.netty/netty/3.2.2.Final/reachability-metadata.json:17:        \"typeReached\" : \"org.jboss.netty.handler.codec.serialization.ObjectDecoderInputStream\"\nmetadata/org.jboss.netty/netty/3.2.2.Final/reachability-metadata.json:24:        \"typeReached\" : \"org.jboss.netty.handler.codec.serialization.ObjectDecoderInputStream\"\nmetadata/org.jboss.netty/netty/3.2.2.Final/reachability-metadata.json:31:        \"typeReached\" : \"org.jboss.netty.handler.codec.serialization.CompactObjectInputStream\"\nmetadata/commons-lang/commons-lang/index.json:27:    \"description\" : \"Apache Commons Lang provides Java utility classes that extend core language functionality for strings, numbers, objects, system properties, serialization, exceptions, and builder-style helpers. Version 1.0 is a JVM library packaged as a JAR for use by Java applications.\",\nmetadata/redis.clients/jedis/3.6.0/reachability-metadata.json:39:  \"serialization\": [\nmetadata/redis.clients/jedis/4.0.0/reachability-metadata.json:62:  \"serialization\": [\nmetadata/io.github.pdvrieze.xmlutil/core-jvmcommon/index.json:9:    \"description\" : \"XMLUtil core-jvmcommon is the Kotlin JVM-common core module of XMLUtil, providing XML streaming, reader/writer, namespace, QName, DOM-like, and utility APIs shared by the JVM and Android-specific core artifacts. It supports Kotlin Multiplatform XML processing and underpins XML serialization integrations while packaging standard JVM class files for use from JVM code.\",\nmetadata/io.github.pdvrieze.xmlutil/serialization-jvm/index.json:5:    \"source-code-url\" : \"https://repo1.maven.org/maven2/io/github/pdvrieze/xmlutil/serialization-jvm/$version$/serialization-jvm-$version$-sources.jar\",\nmetadata/io.github.pdvrieze.xmlutil/serialization-jvm/index.json:7:    \"test-code-url\" : \"https://github.com/pdvrieze/xmlutil/tree/v$version$/serialization/src/jvmTest\",\nmetadata/io.github.pdvrieze.xmlutil/serialization-jvm/index.json:8:    \"documentation-url\" : \"https://repo1.maven.org/maven2/io/github/pdvrieze/xmlutil/serialization-jvm/$version$/serialization-jvm-$version$-javadoc.jar\",\nmetadata/io.github.pdvrieze.xmlutil/serialization-jvm/index.json:9:    \"description\" : \"XMLUtil serialization-jvm is the JVM artifact of XMLUtil's Kotlin XML serialization module, providing a kotlinx.serialization format for encoding and decoding Kotlin @Serializable objects as XML. It builds on XMLUtil's core XML APIs and supplies annotations, configuration policies, serializers, and platform-specific JVM support for controlling XML names, namespaces, attributes, values, and polymorphic structures.\",\nmetadata/io.github.pdvrieze.xmlutil/serialization-jvm/index.json:21:      \"nl.adaptivity.xmlutil.serialization\"\nmetadata/org.scala-lang.modules/scala-xml_2.13/index.json:9:    \"description\" : \"scala-xml is the standard Scala XML library, providing Scala APIs for XML literals, node trees, attributes, parsing, serialization, and pretty printing. It is distributed separately from the Scala compiler so Scala 2 applications can depend on XML support only when they need it.\",\nmetadata/org.scala-lang.modules/scala-xml_2.13/index.json:32:    \"description\" : \"scala-xml is the standard Scala XML library, providing Scala APIs for XML literals, node trees, attributes, parsing, serialization, and pretty printing. It is distributed separately from the Scala compiler so Scala 2 applications can depend on XML support only when they need it.\",\nmetadata/org.objenesis/objenesis/index.json:9:    \"description\" : \"Objenesis is a Java library for instantiating objects without invoking their constructors. It is commonly used by serialization, proxying, and mocking frameworks that need to create objects beyond standard reflection.\",\nmetadata/org.apache.avro/avro/index.json:8:    \"description\" : \"Apache Avro is a data serialization system with a compact binary format, JSON schema definitions, and support for schema evolution. The org.apache.avro:avro artifact provides the Java core APIs for defining schemas and reading and writing generic, specific, reflect, and file-encoded Avro data.\",\nmetadata/org.apache.avro/avro/index.json:23:    \"description\" : \"Apache Avro is a Java library for working with Avro schemas and compact binary data serialization. It provides the core runtime APIs for schema parsing, binary encoding and decoding, datum readers and writers, and generic, specific, and reflective data models.\",\nmetadata/net.minidev/json-smart/index.json:8:    \"description\" : \"json-smart is a compact Java library for parsing and generating JSON with object, array, parser, and serialization APIs. It is designed for JVM applications that need lightweight JSON handling and includes mapper support for converting between JSON values and Java objects.\",\nmetadata/net.minidev/json-smart/index.json:54:    \"description\" : \"json-smart is a small, fast Java library for parsing and generating JSON. It provides JSON object and array models, parser APIs, and serialization helpers for JVM applications.\",\nmetadata/org.apache.pekko/pekko-protobuf-v3_2.13/1.1.5/reachability-metadata.json:189:  \"serialization\" : [\nmetadata/org.apache.pekko/pekko-protobuf-v3_2.13/2.0.0-M2/reachability-metadata.json:407:  \"serialization\" : [\nmetadata/org.apache.pekko/pekko-protobuf-v3_2.13/1.2.0/reachability-metadata.json:403:  \"serialization\" : [\nmetadata/org.apache.pekko/pekko-protobuf-v3_2.13/index.json:6:    \"test-code-url\" : \"https://github.com/apache/pekko/blob/v$version$-RC1/remote/src/test/scala/org/apache/pekko/remote/serialization/ProtobufSerializerSpec.scala\",\nmetadata/org.apache.pekko/pekko-protobuf-v3_2.13/index.json:8:    \"description\" : \"Apache Pekko Protobuf V3 packages a shaded Google Protocol Buffers v3 Java runtime under the org.apache.pekko.protobufv3.internal namespace for Pekko modules. It lets Pekko use protobuf serialization without exposing or conflicting with application-level protobuf dependencies.\",\nmetadata/org.apache.pekko/pekko-protobuf-v3_2.13/index.json:26:    \"test-code-url\" : \"https://github.com/apache/pekko/blob/v$version$/remote/src/test/scala/org/apache/pekko/remote/serialization/ProtobufSerializerSpec.scala\",\nmetadata/org.apache.pekko/pekko-protobuf-v3_2.13/index.json:28:    \"description\" : \"Apache Pekko Protobuf V3 packages a shaded Google Protocol Buffers v3 Java runtime under the org.apache.pekko.protobufv3.internal namespace for Pekko modules. It lets Pekko use protobuf serialization without exposing or conflicting with application-level protobuf dependencies.\",\nmetadata/org.apache.pekko/pekko-protobuf-v3_2.13/index.json:45:    \"test-code-url\" : \"https://github.com/apache/pekko/blob/v$version$/remote/src/test/scala/org/apache/pekko/remote/serialization/ProtobufSerializerSpec.scala\",\nmetadata/org.apache.pekko/pekko-protobuf-v3_2.13/index.json:47:    \"description\" : \"Apache Pekko Protobuf V3 packages the Google Protocol Buffers Java runtime shaded under org.apache.pekko.protobufv3.internal for use by Pekko modules. The relocation lets Pekko depend on protobuf serialization internals without exposing or conflicting with applications' own com.google.protobuf dependencies.\",\nmetadata/org.apache.pekko/pekko-protobuf-v3_2.13/index.json:65:    \"description\" : \"Apache Pekko Protobuf V3 packages the Google Protocol Buffers Java runtime shaded under org.apache.pekko.protobufv3.internal for use by Pekko modules. The relocation lets Pekko depend on protobuf serialization internals without exposing or conflicting with applications' own com.google.protobuf dependencies.\",\nmetadata/org.apache.pekko/pekko-protobuf-v3_2.13/1.6.0/reachability-metadata.json:381:  \"serialization\" : [\nmetadata/org.apache.pekko/pekko-protobuf-v3_3/2.0.0-M2/reachability-metadata.json:403:  \"serialization\" : [\nmetadata/org.apache.pekko/pekko-protobuf-v3_3/1.2.0/reachability-metadata.json:403:  \"serialization\" : [\nmetadata/org.apache.pekko/pekko-protobuf-v3_3/index.json:7:    \"test-code-url\" : \"https://github.com/apache/pekko/blob/v$version$/remote/src/test/scala/org/apache/pekko/remote/serialization/ProtobufSerializerSpec.scala\",\nmetadata/org.apache.pekko/pekko-protobuf-v3_3/index.json:9:    \"description\" : \"Apache Pekko Protobuf V3 packages the Google Protocol Buffers Java runtime shaded under org.apache.pekko.protobufv3.internal for use by Pekko modules. The relocation lets Pekko depend on protobuf serialization internals without exposing or conflicting with applications' own com.google.protobuf dependencies.\",\nmetadata/org.apache.pekko/pekko-protobuf-v3_3/index.json:26:    \"test-code-url\" : \"https://github.com/apache/pekko/blob/v$version$/remote/src/test/scala/org/apache/pekko/remote/serialization/ProtobufSerializerSpec.scala\",\nmetadata/org.apache.pekko/pekko-protobuf-v3_3/index.json:28:    \"description\" : \"Apache Pekko Protobuf V3 packages the Google Protocol Buffers Java runtime shaded under org.apache.pekko.protobufv3.internal for use by Pekko modules. The relocation lets Pekko depend on protobuf serialization internals without exposing or conflicting with applications' own com.google.protobuf dependencies.\",\nmetadata/org.apache.pekko/pekko-protobuf-v3_3/index.json:52:    \"description\" : \"Apache Pekko Protobuf V3 packages the Google Protocol Buffers Java runtime shaded under org.apache.pekko.protobufv3.internal for use by Pekko modules. The relocation lets Pekko depend on protobuf serialization internals without exposing or conflicting with applications' own com.google.protobuf dependencies.\",\nmetadata/org.apache.pekko/pekko-protobuf-v3_3/1.0.1/reachability-metadata.json:128:  \"serialization\" : [\nmetadata/io.ktor/ktor-websocket-serialization/index.json:4:    \"reason\": \"This Kotlin multiplatform metadata artifact contains no JVM .class files; JVM consumers resolve the dedicated ktor-websocket-serialization-jvm artifact.\",\nmetadata/io.ktor/ktor-websocket-serialization/index.json:5:    \"replacement\": \"io.ktor:ktor-websocket-serialization-jvm:3.4.2\"\nmetadata/com.google.flatbuffers/flatbuffers-java/index.json:9:    \"description\" : \"FlatBuffers Java is the Java runtime API for Google's FlatBuffers serialization format, which stores structured data in compact binary buffers that can be read without unpacking. It provides builders, table/vector accessors, and FlexBuffers support used by generated Java code to create and inspect FlatBuffer messages.\",\nmetadata/io.ktor/ktor-serialization-kotlinx-jvm/index.json:5:    \"source-code-url\" : \"https://repo.maven.apache.org/maven2/io/ktor/ktor-serialization-kotlinx-jvm/$version$/ktor-serialization-kotlinx-jvm-$version$-sources.jar\",\nmetadata/io.ktor/ktor-serialization-kotlinx-jvm/index.json:7:    \"test-code-url\" : \"https://github.com/ktorio/ktor/tree/$version$/ktor-shared/ktor-serialization/ktor-serialization-kotlinx/ktor-serialization-kotlinx-tests/jvm/src\",\nmetadata/io.ktor/ktor-serialization-kotlinx-jvm/index.json:8:    \"documentation-url\" : \"https://repo.maven.apache.org/maven2/io/ktor/ktor-serialization-kotlinx-jvm/$version$/ktor-serialization-kotlinx-jvm-$version$-javadoc.jar\",\nmetadata/io.ktor/ktor-serialization-kotlinx-jvm/index.json:9:    \"description\" : \"Ktor Serialization Kotlinx provides Ktor content converters backed by kotlinx.serialization for Kotlin applications. Its JVM artifact supplies the shared converter and WebSocket serialization support used by Ktor clients and servers to serialize and deserialize payloads with kotlinx.serialization formats.\",\nmetadata/io.ktor/ktor-serialization-kotlinx-jvm/index.json:31:      \"io.ktor.serialization.kotlinx\"\nmetadata/io.ktor/ktor-serialization-kotlinx-json-jvm/index.json:5:    \"source-code-url\" : \"https://repo.maven.apache.org/maven2/io/ktor/ktor-serialization-kotlinx-json-jvm/$version$/ktor-serialization-kotlinx-json-jvm-$version$-sources.jar\",\nmetadata/io.ktor/ktor-serialization-kotlinx-json-jvm/index.json:7:    \"test-code-url\" : \"https://github.com/ktorio/ktor/tree/$version$/ktor-shared/ktor-serialization/ktor-serialization-kotlinx/ktor-serialization-kotlinx-json\",\nmetadata/io.ktor/ktor-serialization-kotlinx-json-jvm/index.json:8:    \"documentation-url\" : \"https://repo.maven.apache.org/maven2/io/ktor/ktor-serialization-kotlinx-json-jvm/$version$/ktor-serialization-kotlinx-json-jvm-$version$-javadoc.jar\",\nmetadata/io.ktor/ktor-serialization-kotlinx-json-jvm/index.json:9:    \"description\" : \"Ktor Serialization Kotlinx JSON provides Ktor content conversion support backed by kotlinx.serialization's JSON format. It lets Kotlin/JVM clients and servers encode and decode HTTP request and response bodies as JSON when installing Ktor content negotiation.\",\nmetadata/io.ktor/ktor-serialization-kotlinx-json-jvm/index.json:31:      \"io.ktor.serialization.kotlinx.json\"\nmetadata/net.razorvine/pickle/index.json:9:    \"description\" : \"Pickle is a Java implementation of Python's pickle serialization protocol for reading and writing pickle data. It maps common Python objects to Java types during unpickling and can serialize Java values back into Python-compatible pickle streams.\",\nmetadata/io.ktor/ktor-serialization-kotlinx-protobuf-jvm/index.json:5:    \"source-code-url\" : \"https://repo.maven.apache.org/maven2/io/ktor/ktor-serialization-kotlinx-protobuf-jvm/$version$/ktor-serialization-kotlinx-protobuf-jvm-$version$-sources.jar\",\nmetadata/io.ktor/ktor-serialization-kotlinx-protobuf-jvm/index.json:7:    \"test-code-url\" : \"https://github.com/ktorio/ktor/tree/$version$/ktor-shared/ktor-serialization/ktor-serialization-kotlinx/ktor-serialization-kotlinx-protobuf\",\nmetadata/io.ktor/ktor-serialization-kotlinx-protobuf-jvm/index.json:8:    \"documentation-url\" : \"https://repo.maven.apache.org/maven2/io/ktor/ktor-serialization-kotlinx-protobuf-jvm/$version$/ktor-serialization-kotlinx-protobuf-jvm-$version$-javadoc.jar\",\nmetadata/io.ktor/ktor-serialization-kotlinx-protobuf-jvm/index.json:9:    \"description\" : \"Ktor Serialization Kotlinx ProtoBuf provides Ktor content conversion support backed by kotlinx.serialization's ProtoBuf format. It lets Kotlin/JVM clients and servers encode and decode HTTP request and response bodies as Protocol Buffers when installing Ktor content negotiation.\",\nmetadata/io.ktor/ktor-serialization-kotlinx-protobuf-jvm/index.json:19:      \"io.ktor.serialization.kotlinx.protobuf\"\nmetadata/io.ktor/ktor-server-websockets-jvm/index.json:9:    \"description\" : \"Ktor Server WebSockets is the JVM artifact for Ktor's server-side WebSockets plugin, adding routing handlers and session APIs for WebSocket endpoints in Kotlin server applications. It integrates WebSocket upgrades, frame handling, ping/pong configuration, and optional content-negotiation serialization with Ktor server engines.\",\nmetadata/io.ktor/ktor-websocket-serialization-jvm/index.json:5:    \"source-code-url\" : \"https://repo.maven.apache.org/maven2/io/ktor/ktor-websocket-serialization-jvm/$version$/ktor-websocket-serialization-jvm-$version$-sources.jar\",\nmetadata/io.ktor/ktor-websocket-serialization-jvm/index.json:8:    \"documentation-url\" : \"https://github.com/ktorio/ktor-documentation/blob/$version$/topics/server-websocket-serialization.md\",\nmetadata/io.ktor/ktor-websocket-serialization-jvm/index.json:31:      \"io.ktor.websocket.serialization\"\nmetadata/com.google.protobuf/protobuf-javalite/index.json:9:    \"description\" : \"Protocol Buffers is a binary serialization format and runtime for encoding structured data efficiently across services and storage systems. protobuf-javalite provides the size-optimized Java Lite runtime for generated protobuf messages, trading some API/ABI stability for smaller deployments.\",\nmetadata/com.google.protobuf/protobuf-javalite/index.json:24:    \"description\" : \"Protocol Buffers is a binary serialization format and runtime for encoding structured data efficiently across services and storage systems. protobuf-javalite provides the size-optimized Java Lite runtime for generated protobuf messages, trading some API/ABI stability for smaller deployments.\",\nmetadata/com.google.protobuf/protobuf-java/2.5.0/reachability-metadata.json:126:  \"serialization\": [\nmetadata/net.sf.kxml/kxml2/index.json:9:    \"description\" : \"kXML 2 is a small XML pull parser based on the common XML Pull API. It is designed for constrained Java environments such as applets, PersonalJava, and MIDP devices and includes XML serialization, kDOM, and WBXML support.\",\nmetadata/org.seleniumhq.selenium/selenium-json/index.json:9:    \"description\" : \"Selenium JSON provides the JSON serialization and deserialization utilities used by Selenium's Java components. It reads and writes JSON values, maps, collections, and Selenium domain objects so WebDriver commands and responses can be converted between Java objects and wire-format JSON.\",\nmetadata/io.ktor/ktor-server-content-negotiation-jvm/index.json:8:    \"documentation-url\" : \"https://github.com/ktorio/ktor-documentation/blob/$version$/topics/server-serialization.md\",\nmetadata/com.fasterxml.jackson.datatype/jackson-datatype-jdk8/index.json:9:    \"description\" : \"Jackson Datatype JDK8 is an add-on module for Jackson Databind that adds serialization and deserialization support for Java 8 types such as Optional, OptionalInt, OptionalLong, and OptionalDouble. It lets ObjectMapper handle those JDK 8 container types through Jackson's standard module registration mechanism.\",\nmetadata/org.hibernate.orm/hibernate-core/6.1.1.Final/reachability-metadata.json:31:      \"type\": \"com.fasterxml.jackson.databind.DeserializationFeature\",\nmetadata/com.fasterxml.jackson.datatype/jackson-datatype-jsr310/index.json:9:    \"description\" : \"Jackson Datatype JSR310 is an add-on module for Jackson that adds serialization and deserialization support for Java 8 Date and Time API types. It lets ObjectMapper handle java.time classes such as LocalDate, LocalDateTime, OffsetDateTime, and Instant using Jackson's standard module registration mechanism.\",\nmetadata/com.fasterxml.jackson.datatype/jackson-datatype-jsr310/index.json:23:    \"description\" : \"Jackson Datatype JSR310 is an add-on module for Jackson that adds serialization and deserialization support for Java 8 Date and Time API types. It lets ObjectMapper handle java.time classes such as LocalDate, LocalDateTime, OffsetDateTime, and Instant using Jackson's standard module registration mechanism.\",\nmetadata/net.razorvine/pyrolite/index.json:24:    \"description\" : \"Pyrolite lets Java applications interact with Python services over the Pyro protocol by invoking methods on remote Python objects. It includes Python pickle serialization support for reading and writing data exchanged with Pyro and Python.\",\nmetadata/tools.jackson.core/jackson-databind/index.json:9:    \"description\" : \"Jackson Databind provides general-purpose object mapping and tree-model support for converting between Java objects and structured data using Jackson's streaming API. It is most commonly used for JSON serialization and deserialization, while also supporting other data formats when matching Jackson parser and generator modules are available.\",\nmetadata/com.datastax.oss/native-protocol/index.json:9:    \"description\" : \"DataStax Native Protocol is a Java implementation of the Apache Cassandra native protocol. It provides frame and message model types with serialization and deserialization logic for Cassandra and DataStax Enterprise protocol variants.\",\nmetadata/com.lihaoyi/upack_3/index.json:9:    \"description\" : \"uPack is the MessagePack component of uPickle, providing an in-memory MessagePack data model plus readers and writers for parsing and serializing MessagePack bytes. It is published for Scala 3 and integrates with uPickle's visitor-based serialization infrastructure.\",\nmetadata/com.lihaoyi/upickle-implicits_3/index.json:9:    \"description\" : \"uPickle is a Scala JSON and MessagePack serialization library for reading and writing structured data. The upickle-implicits module supplies macro and implicit derivation of readers and writers for Scala data types, including case classes, enums, tuples, and collections.\",\nmetadata/com.thoughtworks.proxytoys/proxytoys/1.0/reachability-metadata.json:318:  \"serialization\" : [\nmetadata/org.apache.maven/maven-support/index.json:9:    \"description\" : \"Maven Support provides the generated support layer for Maven 4 model-related data, including readers, writers, mergers, transformers, and model-version helpers. It handles XML serialization support for Maven project models, settings, toolchains, repository metadata, plugin descriptors, and plugin lifecycle descriptors used by Maven's implementation.\",\nmetadata/com.lihaoyi/ujson_3/index.json:9:    \"description\" : \"ujson is the JSON AST and parser/rendering component of uPickle, a Scala JSON and MessagePack serialization library. It provides Scala data types and APIs for reading, transforming, and writing JSON values, published here as a Scala 3 JVM artifact.\",\nmetadata/com.lihaoyi/ujson_3/index.json:30:    \"description\" : \"ujson is the JSON AST and parser/rendering component of uPickle, a Scala JSON and MessagePack serialization library. It provides Scala data types and APIs for reading, transforming, and writing JSON values, published here as a Scala 3 JVM artifact.\",\nmetadata/com.lihaoyi/upickle_3/index.json:9:    \"description\" : \"uPickle is a Scala JSON and MessagePack serialization library for reading and writing structured data. The upickle_3 artifact provides the Scala 3 JVM API that combines JSON and MessagePack readers, writers, macro derivation, and default serialization helpers for application code.\",\nmetadata/com.lihaoyi/upickle_3/index.json:30:    \"description\" : \"uPickle is a Scala JSON and MessagePack serialization library for reading and writing structured data. The upickle_3 artifact provides the Scala 3 JVM API that combines JSON and MessagePack readers, writers, macro derivation, and default serialization helpers for application code.\",\nmetadata/com.clickhouse/clickhouse-data/index.json:9:    \"description\" : \"ClickHouse Data provides Java utilities for processing ClickHouse data values and formats without requiring a live ClickHouse connection. It includes support for type mapping, value conversion, serialization, streaming, and compression used by ClickHouse Java client components.\",\nmetadata/io.netty/netty-codec/4.1.42.Final/reachability-metadata.json:38:        \"typeReached\" : \"io.netty.handler.codec.serialization.ObjectEncoderOutputStream\"\nmetadata/io.netty/netty-codec/4.1.42.Final/reachability-metadata.json:123:        \"typeReached\" : \"io.netty.handler.codec.serialization.CompactObjectOutputStream\"\nmetadata/io.netty/netty-codec/index.json:9:    \"description\" : \"Netty Codec provides encoders and decoders for transforming byte streams and messages within Netty channel pipelines. It includes reusable frame decoders, compression handlers, serialization codecs, and protocol-building primitives used by Netty-based network applications.\",\nmetadata/com.akuleshov7/ktoml-core-jvm/index.json:9:    \"description\" : \"KToml is a Kotlin Multiplatform TOML library built on kotlinx.serialization for parsing, encoding, and decoding TOML documents. The ktoml-core-jvm artifact provides the JVM implementation of its core serializer/deserializer, AST parser, annotations, configuration, and TOML writer APIs.\",\nmetadata/io.netty/netty-all/4.0.23.Final/reachability-metadata.json:11:        \"typeReached\" : \"io.netty.handler.codec.serialization.CompactObjectInputStream\"\nmetadata/io.netty/netty-all/4.0.23.Final/reachability-metadata.json:17:        \"typeReached\" : \"io.netty.handler.codec.serialization.ObjectDecoder\"\nmetadata/io.netty/netty-all/4.0.23.Final/reachability-metadata.json:228:        \"typeReached\" : \"io.netty.handler.codec.serialization.CompatibleObjectEncoder\"\nmetadata/io.netty/netty-all/4.0.23.Final/reachability-metadata.json:246:        \"typeReached\" : \"io.netty.handler.codec.serialization.CompatibleObjectEncoder\"\nmetadata/io.netty/netty-all/4.0.23.Final/reachability-metadata.json:285:        \"typeReached\" : \"io.netty.handler.codec.serialization.CompatibleObjectEncoder\"\nmetadata/io.netty/netty-all/4.0.23.Final/reachability-metadata.json:398:        \"typeReached\" : \"io.netty.handler.codec.serialization.CompactObjectOutputStream\"\nmetadata/io.fabric8/kubernetes-model-core/index.json:9:    \"description\" : \"kubernetes-model-core provides the core Java model classes for Kubernetes API resources used by the Fabric8 Kubernetes client. It includes generated and handwritten types, builders, and serializatio